## API Call - URL Description
|API Call|Method|URL Endpoint|Description|
|-----------|--------|-------|-------------|
|login|POST|/api/login|To authenticate the user|
|getContext|GET|/api/1/CtxDto|To get the panchayat data ex: State, District, Division, Mandal, Panchayat etc..|
|surveyUser|PUT|/api/1/SurveyUser |To Put the survey user in the server|
|pushOtpData|PUT|/api/1/SurveyUserOtp |To Push the OTP data ex: email OTP, Mobile OTP etc.. |
|signUpUserLogout|GET|/api/logout|To logout the SignUp user|


### Description :

1. Get hostname from database. If the hostname is null from database then refer Routing API to get Host name **[Routing API](http://localhost:1313/productspecification/features/mobileapplication/api/routing-api/)**  
2. In the UserConfirmation screen invoke the api call (1) invokeRegisterAuth (https://{hostname}/api/login) API  
    - If the response is 200 - save the response data (authToken, jwtToken) to PreferenceHelper preference and invoke the api call getContext ( https://{hostname}/api/{apiVer}/CtxDto )  
3. If the response from api call getContext is 200 then save the response data (hazelcastId) in Preference Helper preference and invoke the api call surveyUser (https://{hostname}/1/SurveyUser).  
    - if response is 400 or any other code - show error message
4. If the response from api call surveyUser is 200 then navigate the user to OtpVerification screen.  
   - if response is 400 or any other code - show error message  
5. In the OtpVerification screen invoke the api call pushOtpData (https://{hostname}/1/SurveyUserOtp) API  
   - 5.1 If the response is 200 - navigate the user to SignUpSuccess screen  
   If the response is other than 200   
   - 5.2 If response is 401 - check failedToken value and it is equal to unsuccessful then navigate the user to the login page for re-login.  
   - 5.3 If response is 401 & failedToken value is null then get the user object from database and invoke login API calls steps 1 & 2 in login API - reference for Login API step 1,2 [Login API](http://localhost:1313/productspecification/features/mobileapplication/api/login-api/)  
    if the response from getContext api call is 200 then repeat step (4)  
6. In the SignUpSuccess screen invoke the api call signUpUserLogout (https://{hostname}/api/logout)  
    - If the response is other than 200 show error message

### Flow of SignUp API Calls
#### Reference for Routing API [Routing API](http://localhost:1313/productspecification/features/mobileapplication/api/routing-api/)  
{{<mermaid align="center">}}
graph TD 
	start((Start))
	GetHostNameFromDB{DB Call: Get RouteData}
	RoutingApi[Refer : Routing API Flow Diagram]
	UserConfirmationPage[userConfirmation Page]
	InvokeRegisterAuthApiCall{ API Call : invokeRegisterAuth }
	GetContextApiCall{API Call : getContext }
	InvokeRegisterAPI{API Call : surveyUser }
	OtpVerificationPage[OTPVerificationPage]
	PushOtpDataApiCall{API Call : pushOtpData}
	SignUpSuccessPage[SignUpSuccess Page]
	ResponseFailedToken{Response FailedToken}
	FailedTokenUnSuccessCheck{FailedToken == unsuccessful}
	LoginPage[LoginPage]
	GoToInvokeRegisterApiCall[Go To Step : InvokeRegisterAPICall]
    SignUpUserLogoutApiCall{Api Call : singUpUserLogout}
	error1>error]
	error2>error]
	error3>error]
	error4>error]
    error5>error]
	end1((end))
	
	
	start-->GetHostNameFromDB
	subgraph SignUpFormPage
	    GetHostNameFromDB--RouteData==NULL-->RoutingApi
	    RoutingApi-->UserConfirmationPage
	end
	
	subgraph UserConfirmation Page
	    UserConfirmationPage-->InvokeRegisterAuthApiCall
        InvokeRegisterAuthApiCall--Response!=200-->error1
    	InvokeRegisterAuthApiCall--Response==200-->GetContextApiCall
    	GetContextApiCall--Response!=200-->error2
        GetContextApiCall--Response==200-->InvokeRegisterAPI
        InvokeRegisterAPI--Response!=200-->error3
        InvokeRegisterAPI--Response==200-->OtpVerificationPage
	end
	
	subgraph OTPVerification Page
        OtpVerificationPage-->PushOtpDataApiCall
        PushOtpDataApiCall--Response==Other-->error4
        PushOtpDataApiCall--Response==200-->SignUpSuccessPage
        PushOtpDataApiCall--Response==401-->ResponseFailedToken
        ResponseFailedToken--NotNULL-->FailedTokenUnSuccessCheck
        FailedTokenUnSuccessCheck--true-->LoginPage
        ResponseFailedToken--NULL-->GoToInvokeRegisterApiCall

        SignUpSuccessPage-->SignUpUserLogoutApiCall
        SignUpUserLogoutApiCall--Response!=200-->error5
        SignUpUserLogoutApiCall--Response==200-->end1
    end
